    • build

      public final void build(org.objectweb.asm.commons.GeneratorAdapter method, org.objectweb.asm.Type initialType, Stream<SignableRenderer> variables)
      Description copied from class: SignatureDefinition
      Generate bytecode to produce the signature

      This method operates different depending on the storage of the signature.

      • If the signature does not actually depend on the input (SignatureStorage.STATIC), then the method passed will be a clinit method and the constant value should be pushed on the stack.
      • If the signature depends on the input (SignatureStorage.DYNAMIC), then the method passed will be a method that takes one input, the stream variable to be signed, and the resulting value should be pushed on the stack.
      Specified by:
      build in class SignatureDefinition
      Parameters:
      method - the method in which to generate the byte code
      initialType - the type of the input data
      variables - the input variables to capture
